<!-- Overview -->
<div class="overview-section">
<h2>What Is Economic Analysis for Personal Injury?</h2>
<p>As a forensic economist in Rhode Island, we provide comprehensive economic damages analysis for catastrophic injury and wrongful death cases. Our expert calculations of lost earnings, diminished earning capacity, and future care costs help attorneys throughout New England build stronger cases and achieve fair compensation for their clients. With over 20 years of experience as a vocational expert and forensic economist, we deliver court-tested opinions that withstand scrutiny.</p>
<p>Economic analysis in personal injury cases involves quantifying all financial losses resulting from an injury or death. This includes past and future lost earnings, fringe benefits, household services, and life care costs. Our Rhode Island-based firm specializes in creating detailed economic reports that comply with state-specific requirements and federal court reliability standards, ensuring admissibility in all New England courts.</p>
<p>Our personal injury economic damage calculations consider multiple factors including age, education, work history, earning capacity, and injury severity. We collaborate with medical professionals, vocational rehabilitation specialists, and life care planners to develop comprehensive damage assessments that capture the full economic impact of injuries on victims and their families.</p>
</div>
