<!-- When Expert Needed Section -->
<div class="expert-needed-section">
<h2>When Is an Economic Expert Needed?</h2>
<p>Personal injury attorneys in Rhode Island and throughout New England rely on economic experts in cases involving:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Catastrophic injuries</strong> with permanent disability or reduced work capacity</li>
<li><strong>High-earning professionals</strong> where future income loss is substantial</li>
<li><strong>Young victims</strong> requiring lifetime earnings projections</li>
<li><strong>Self-employed individuals</strong> with complex income documentation</li>
<li><strong>Wrongful death cases</strong> requiring household services and support calculations</li>
</ul>
<p>Early involvement of a forensic economist ensures comprehensive damage documentation and stronger case presentations.</p>
</div>
<!-- Services Section -->
<div class="services-detailed">
<h2>How We Calculate Damages</h2>
<div class="service-item">
<h3>Lost Earnings &amp; Earning Capacity</h3>
<p>We calculate both past lost earnings from the time of injury and future earning capacity losses over the individual's remaining work life. Our analyses consider career progression, wage growth trends, and economic factors specific to the individual's industry and geographic region.</p>
<ul>
<li>Historical earnings analysis using tax records and employment data</li>
<li>Future earning capacity projections based on career trajectory</li>
<li>Industry-specific wage growth analysis</li>
<li>Present value calculations using appropriate discount rates</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="service-item">
<h3>Fringe Benefits &amp; Employment Perquisites</h3>
<p>Beyond base wages, we quantify the full value of employment benefits including health insurance, retirement contributions, paid time off, and other perquisites that would have been earned over the individual's career.</p>
<ul>
<li>Health insurance and medical benefits valuation</li>
<li>Retirement and pension contribution losses</li>
<li>Paid vacation and sick leave calculations</li>
<li>Stock options and incentive compensation analysis</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="service-item">
<h3>Household Services Replacement</h3>
<p>For individuals unable to perform household tasks due to injury, we calculate the economic value of lost household services including childcare, home maintenance, and other domestic activities.</p>
<ul>
<li>Childcare and family care services</li>
<li>Home maintenance and yard work</li>
<li>Household management and financial services</li>
<li>Transportation and errand services</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="service-item">
<h3>Life Care Cost Analysis</h3>
<p>For catastrophic injuries requiring ongoing care, we work with life care planners to quantify the present value of future medical expenses, equipment needs, and care services.</p>
<ul>
<li>Medical treatment and therapy costs</li>
<li>Pharmaceutical and medical supply expenses</li>
<li>Durable medical equipment and assistive technology</li>
<li>Home modifications and accessibility improvements</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
