<!-- Case Examples Section -->
<div class="case-examples-section">
<h2>Case Examples</h2>
<div class="case-example">
<h4>Construction Worker Spinal Injury</h4>
<p>Calculated $2.4 million in lost earnings and benefits for a 35-year-old union carpenter who suffered permanent partial disability. Analysis included union wage scales, prevailing wage opportunities, and reduced work capacity assessment.</p>
</div>
<div class="case-example">
<h4>Medical Professional Brain Injury</h4>
<p>Provided economic damages analysis for a physician unable to practice following traumatic brain injury. Quantified $8.5 million in lost income, practice value, and retirement benefits through detailed specialty-specific earnings analysis.</p>
</div>
<div class="case-example">
<h4>Young Adult Wrongful Death</h4>
<p>Calculated economic support loss for parents of a 22-year-old college student. Projected career earnings based on education path and family occupation history.</p>
