<!-- Methodology Section -->
<div class="methodology-section">
<h2>Our Methodology &amp; Court-Ready Analysis</h2>
<p>As expert forensic economists, we follow established forensic economics principles and comply with court reliability standards for expert testimony. We utilize peer-reviewed methodologies and current economic data to ensure reliability and admissibility.</p>
<p>Our economic damages personal injury calculations incorporate the latest research in forensic economics, including worklife expectancy studies, wage growth projections, and discount rate analysis. We maintain extensive databases of occupation-specific earnings data for Rhode Island and New England, enabling precise calculations tailored to each client's unique circumstances. Our reports clearly document all assumptions and methodologies, providing transparent and defensible economic opinions.</p>
<div class="methodology-grid">
<div class="method-item">
<h4>Data Sources</h4>
<ul>
<li>Bureau of Labor Statistics wage surveys</li>
<li>Census Bureau demographic data</li>
<li>Social Security Administration life tables</li>
<li>Federal Reserve economic indicators</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="method-item">
<h4>Calculation Methods</h4>
<ul>
<li>Worklife expectancy (Skoog-Ciecka tables)</li>
<li>Present value calculations (Treasury rates)</li>
<li>Real wage growth projections</li>
<li>Statistical probability adjustments</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
